Praia do Sancho, Fernando de Noronha
Many people - including myself - claim Praia do Sancho is the most beautiful beach in Brazil. Crescent-shaped, it is guarded by a high cliff wall. You can only reach it by boat or descending the cliff through an iron staircase on a crack on the rock. It's crystal-clear waters are a diver's paradise. Have a look in <a href="http://maps.google.com/?ie=UTF8&amp;ll=-3.853914,-32.443099&amp;spn=0.008007,0.013937&amp;t=h&amp;z=17" target=" blank" rel="nofollow">Google Maps</a> to see its location.

<a href="http://www.braziltravelblog.com/2007/03/15/destination-fernando-de-noronha/" rel="nofollow">destination: Fernando de Noronha</a>, lots of travel tips at my blog.
